						span(class="fa fa-flask")
						div.tile-details
							h2 Formula
							p Base = NYSE Advances - NYSE Declines.
							p McClellan Oscillator = 19 day EMA of Base - 39 day EMA of Base.
			div(class="row row-tiles")
				div.col-md-12
					div(class="tile ")
						div.tile-details
							h2 How it works
							p The McClellan Oscillator offers many types of structures for interpretation, but there are two main ones. First, when the Oscillator is positive, it generally portrays money coming into the market; conversely, when it is negative, it reflects money leaving the market. Second, when the oscillator reaches extreme readings, it can reflect an overbought or oversold condition.
							p Divergences between price and Oscillator can be used to detect trend changes. Many more important structures are outlined in the book Patterns For Profit by Sherman and Marian McClellan.To use this indicator in your NinjaTrader you need to have the ^ADD instrument.

							
